# =====================================================
# SETUP GUIDE
# =====================================================
#
# 1. SUPABASE SETUP:
#    a. Create a project at https://supabase.com
#    b. Go to Project Settings → API
#    c. Copy the Project URL and anon/public key
#    d. Go to SQL Editor and run the schema.sql file
#    e. Enable Email Auth in Authentication settings
#
# 2. CLOUDINARY SETUP:
#    a. Create account at https://cloudinary.com
#    b. Get cloud name from dashboard
#    c. Create upload preset in Settings → Upload
#
# 3. ADMIN ACCESS:
#    a. After running schema.sql, use these demo credentials:
#       Email: admin@authenticgirlswear.com
#       Password: admin123
#    b. In production, create admin via Supabase Auth
#
# 4. LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
#    $ npm install
#    $ cp .env.example .env
#    $ npm run dev
#
# 5. DEPLOY TO VERCEL:
#    $ npm install -g vercel
#    $ vercel
#    # Add environment variables in Vercel dashboard
#
# 6. PROJECT STRUCTURE:
#    src/
#    ├── types/          # TypeScript type definitions
#    ├── data/           # Mock data (replace with Supabase queries)
#    ├── store/          # Zustand state management
#    ├── lib/            # Supabase client & helpers
#    ├── components/
#    │   ├── ui/         # Reusable UI components
#    │   ├── layout/     # Navbar, Footer, AdminLayout
#    │   └── home/       # Homepage section components
#    └── pages/
#        ├── Home, Shop, Product, Cart, Checkout, Search, Category
#        └── admin/      # Admin panel pages
#    supabase/
#    └── schema.sql      # Database schema
#
# =====================================================
